  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">GFDRR Recipient Grant for IGAD in Eastern Africa regional risk reduction and sustainable development  Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the collaboration is to: a. Help disaster prone countries, particularly in Sub-Saharan Africa, reduce the risk of disasters, while addressing challenges posed by climate change, and accelerate transition to recovery in the aftermath of a disaster; b. Strengthen disaster risk management capacities of national and sub/regional bodies, parliaments, civil society, and private sector across Africa and beyond; c. Generate and share knowledge and innovation, pooling the existing networks of both institutions, to accelerate implementation of the Hyogo Framework for Action (HFA) in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
